Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph queue add

Purpose:
  Create one generation task for one `.sdpub` chapter.

Usage:
  wikigraph queue add <archive.sdpub> --chapter <id> --task <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]

Options:
  --chapter <id>       Required chapter id.
  --task <task>        Required task: reading-graph, reading-summary, or knowledge-graph.
  --accept-cost        Explicitly acknowledge LLM cost and wait time.
  --boost              Insert the new job at the front of the queued jobs.
  --llm <json>         Override LLM configuration for this job.
  --prompt <text>      Override extraction prompt for this job.

Task choices:
  reading-graph        Build the reading-oriented chunk graph from sourced text.
  reading-summary      Build summaries from the Reading Graph. Builds reading-graph first when needed.
  knowledge-graph      Build entity mentions from sourced text. Required before entity search can return results.

Examples:
  wikigraph queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --task reading-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --task reading-summary --accept-cost --boost
  wikigraph queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --task knowledge-graph --accept-cost
